
<p>Reuters <strong><a href="https://www.reuters.com/business/retail-consumer/hm-says-it-will-phase-out-sourcing-myanmar-2023-08-17/">exclusively reported</a></strong> that the world&#8217;s second-biggest fashion retailer H&amp;M (HMb.ST) has decided to gradually stop sourcing from Myanmar, as reports of labor abuses in garment factories in the country increase.</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.reutersagency.com/en/reutersbest/article/hm-says-it-will-phase-out-sourcing-from-myanmar/">H&amp;M says it will &#8220;phase out&#8221; sourcing from Myanmar</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.reutersagency.com/en/">Reuters News Agency</a>.</p>
